caption: Guy making sushi behind counter was soooo rude!!!! (Assuming he was boss in white coat) At first I made a reservation and they wanted to seat us by the door(it was cold) asked to go in back and he said at first "no theres fine" I asked we made a reservation no one on the whole place why cant we move away feom the door? "Fine, whatever". Then went to sit down, blinds completely closed.. I went to open them and then heard him say to our waiter, "go tell that girl to stop touching everything". (Would you rather the server reach other 2 people to open the blinds for us?? Verse contaminate one little shade, after I had just sanitized my hands?? Mind you... we closed down the place... no one else was coming in. Then.. the server kept asking what else we wanted like we were such an inconvenience being customers.. sushi good but wont be back now.

I cannot stress enough how wonderful our evening was at Sushi Mon this week. We had reservations and were very grateful that Bat and his staff honored them even though they were extremely busy with online and to-go orders. Our waiter was every attentive and the veggie tempura and rolls were dynamite. This was such a wonderful experience and I know we will be back soon. Thank you!
The best place in town! Staff is super nice and the sushi is always great. The fish is fresh and the miso soup that comes with it is excellent! 100% would recommend.
Unreal place! Was ordering from Toro all the timer and never came to this restaurant. Much much much better. Great sushi ! We are coming back very soon!

One of the best sushi spots in the city hands down. The owner Bat is humble and hard-working and loves to get to know his customers. His sushi and other foods are made with great quality and care. Also once COVID-19 is over, his spot is BYOB, how can you beat that?
Always like their sushi
It had most of the Japanese trappings. And the food offerings were good. Taste of the food was great.
Great food.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The the food there is flavorable and the team is generous and cooperative. always when we eat in this place we have a splendid evening.  warmly recommended.
My first Google review because this sushi was DELICIOUS! The tropical geisha roll is to die for. Highly recommend!
Top 2 spot in Lincoln Park hands down.

My absolute FAVORITE sushi place in the city and beyond. Love this place to death. The staff is fantastic, and the sushi SO big and SO delicious. You get your bang for your buck. Always filling. My two go to meals are the Maki Plate E and the Shrimp Udon Soup. The owner even surprised my now husband and I with a free meal when we went in to celebrate our engagement in 2017! Will be eating here every week for as long as I live in Chicago.
I actually loved the food and service, excellent location very close to my home. The cashiers are always very friendly. Would recommend to others.
Wonderful sushi. Chefs daughter has adorable art all over the restaurant.
This place is worth a visit. They have large portions for fair rates. Consistently neat and with awesome character. Will come back again.
Some of the best sushi we've had in a while. Will definitely go back.
Great, fresh sushi for a  reasonable price!

Service was great I’ll give them that, the food was decent as well but the price in comparison to what you get does not add up in my opinion. I’ve been to multiple restaurants that charge less for more.
(Translated by Google) Of the best sushi I have ever eaten !!  (Original) De los mejores sushi que he comido!!
Best sushi in town . Very delicious and beautiful presentation of sushi.
Love it
(Translated by Google) This is the most restaurant like Japanese home cooking.  (Original) 這是一家最像日本家庭料理的餐廳
I come here regularly. Although I eat sushis at least twice a week all over the Midwest (for work), I haven't found anything as good as their Rainbow pressed sushi!

I normally reserve judgement on sushi restaurants until after I've visited a few times so I can try some different rolls, but this time I felt compelled to review right away.  It is very obviously a family-run restaurant and I couldn't have felt more comfortable and welcome.  The food was good as advertised, but the atmosphere would have me coming back regardless.  Will definitely be back.
Best sushi in town! Don’t miss the pressed sushi and ask Bat for the specials!
LOVE LOVE LOVE this place
Go here all the time food is great service is great my favorite sushi place in chicago.
Good spot for sushi

My boyfriend and I came here 8 years ago on our first Valentine's Day date and decided to come again this year. The staff are so nice especially our server. We order different rolls of Sushi and both got Miso Soup. The food didn't take long and it was extremely delicious. I highly recommend this lovely restaurant!
High Quality Sushi
The food and service was excellent!!! Loved the pressed Sushi!! We had the Rainbow pressed...yummy!! Everything was great.

Sushi is ok, but service is lacking. When we went there the server acted bothered to have us there. They misrepresent the specials and deals. They tried to over charge me, luckily i reviewed my receipt. Its nice that they are open 7days a week, but all in all i would go to "Toro Sushi" befor i went back here.
One of the great sushi place in Lincoln Park
Great sushi (try the pressed sushi!), great atmosphere, friendly staff, and quick service. One of my favorite sushi spots!
It’s good
Yummy sushi

Came in on a Saturday night, the restaurant was full and seemed a little short staffed. Our appetizer was not brought out until we asked for a second time. The sushi itself was not fresh and I was disappointed in the quality, however the portion size was pretty big. Would not come back.
Really good quality sushi for an affordable price

This is my favorite sushi spot. Been going there for years. When I walk I feel like a character from "Cheers." The B.G. is superb and Bat usually has hard to get delicacies like uni which is seasonal.

Home of the Sweet Baby Roll! Amazing sushi, amazing staff, the best sushi in Chicago! Delicious and fresh, and reasonably priced. A must stop whenever we are in Chicago for the Sweet Baby and the Sparkling roll.

Food was good. Service was not !! When we ordered for a second round, the service team completely forgot about it. When they tried to make amends - they served incorrect food. When we asked for the plate to be changed - they took out the incorrect dish and served the old plate. That's pretty sad!!

The sushi is so fresh, unique, delicious, and filling. I eat a lot of sushi, and this is the best that I’ve had in a long time. It’s a few dollars pricier than other restaurants I’ve been to, but the saying holds true: you get what you pay for.

This is my go to place for sushi... The salmon appetizer, Red Dragon, Tropical Geisha and Evolution rolls are incredible. I'm a repeat customer and have never been disappointed. The quality is great, it is reasonably priced and the service is the best. It is also BYOB.  They recently expanded the dining room area and can accommodate larger parties.
Fresh fish and big portions. Recommend the salmon and the Chicago Roll.
Delicious sushi and very kind personal!
The best sushi and nicest service!
Fresh, well-prepared sushi with a wide selection of different rolls. Awesome music.
Love it

The fish is incredibly fresh and delicious.
The best place for sushi period. Bat has an amazing selection. Our favorites: Ari, sweet baby, veggie wow, V6, and tropical geisha. The best reason to come to Chicago.
Good food, customer service good
My absolute favorite sushi in Chicago! Love Chef Bat

This is our favorite sushi place discovered many years ago. It only keeps improving. Simply the best in Chicago. Many vegetarian options. Not overpriced. BYOB. Great place to celebrate, to spend time with friends and family.
Great sushi. The pressed sushi was fine, but seemed like too much rice...I’d skip it next time and just get more rolls or nigiri. Solid place.
Everything is so creative and delicious. Service is excellent. You will not be disappointed.

Food is fresh and portions are generous. Bat (pronounced like "bot") and Zaya and the whole Sushi Mon crew are super friendly. They want you to enjoy your meal. Check them out. You'll be glad you did.
Food is very delicious. They serve pressed sushi here which seems like a higher rice comment than a testimony maki roll. Good vegetarian selection of menu items. Service can be lacking at times.
Sushi was tasty, service was good.  Atmosphere was a little cramped.
I used to live in the neighborhood and still miss this place 5 years later because Bat's sushi is just that good.
Bat is an artist, nice portions, great service and only the best fish.

I love this place. My go to place since college, so at least 6 years now. No matter where I go, I still come back to this place. The service is spectacular. The atmosphere is warmth and welcoming. The sushi/sashimi are especially fresh. Btw, it's byob so I always stopped by the liquor a few door down and bring a bottle here.
Have been coming here for 8 years. Staff and food is honestly second to none in the entire city.

Loved the sushi! Loved the service!
Gotta get the pressed sushi roll
Favorite spot to grab sushi in the neighborhood. Exceptionally friendly staff, cozy restaurant and fantastic sushi. Try the tropical geisha roll, you won't regret it.
Red Dragon Roll, Spicy Shrimp Tempura Roll, Vienna Roll, Tai Nigiri !!
Great sushi! Great service! Love the pressed rolls.

I usually order for pickup and eat sushi perhaps twice a month. I have been going to Sushi Mon since it opened. The owner is a gregarious and friendly man. The sushi is always good. My wife doesn't like sushi but does like their grilled salmon entree. But the salmon she received last night was dried out and tasteless. The only reason I am writing this review is in the hope that Sushi Mon will read it and correct  it next time.
Great food niece new dinning area.

Not a big sushi guy, but the time had come to acquiesce to my girlfriend's pleas. The chicken teriyaki was very tasty and went above and beyond any I have sheepishly ordered before at other sushi places. Great sushi restaurant for people who don't like sushi.
Great sushi and huge variety. Meticulously crafted sushi.
Bat is the best

My friend and I ordered the  yellowtail roll and crazy pressed sushi roll and they were both so tasty! That was my first time trying pressed sushi and I really enjoyed it - the roll has more rice but I love rice so it worked in my favor. The pressed sushi also comes with soup and salad and most rolls are $13/$14 so it's a great deal. BYOB and didn't charge a corkage fee. A+ in my book and will come here again!

Best sushi in town for my taste!! Very friendly owner and staff!! Great selection of sushi rolls!! Yellow tail special and spicy scallop hand roll are my favorite!! Recommend to anyone who likes sushi!!!!
Reasonable prices and very good quantity of food they serve you. The sushi is DELICIOUS and the waiter is REALLY friendly I loved her.

The fish is very fresh. Texture was amazing. Went here due to all the five star reviews and I wasn't disappointed one bit. The price is also very good. After a few more times I think this will be my new sushi  spot. Highly recommended!
I recommend this place.  It is reasonably priced and the service staff is friendly and efficient.  BYOB helps the pocket.  All in all, a great dining experience!  Good ambient tunes as well!
Best Sushi in Chicago and they can make almost everything gluten free! I highly recommend!

I rarely review places, but this sushi place is exceptional. I've been to over a dozen of the "most highly rated" sushi places in Chicago, and this one wins by a landslide. Freshest fish I've had in the city - similar in quality to those I had at Shiro's (an apprentice of Jiro) Sushi Restaurant in Seattle, and given Sushi Mon is in Chicago, that's a pretty impressive feat. Great portions, reasonable prices, and probably the best kept secret of LP.
When I die bury my body with tons of Sushi Mon rolls .Covering my casket. Then every year, feed a crow a Sushi Mon roll in honor of me.  THIS PLACE IS AMAZING!!!!
Great pressed sushi!
Great local sushi spot. The owner Bat is awesome.
Very nice service, great food! I would definitely be a regular customer here. It seems like they make food art.
Terrible service. Food ok.
Best and most creative sushi I have eaten. The Veggie Wow was unbeleivably tasty as was the Red Dragon Roll.
Out of the dozen sushi places on Clark, these guys are THE best.  Bat (the chef) is amazingly talented and super nice.  Everyone there is great.  Delicious fresh food and honest prices makes them #1.
Absolutely fantastic. We were headed to Toro Sushi down the street but it was closed. Ended up here but very pleased.

Mu husband's and I favorite place. We would not go to another sushi place. It would be cheating on the best sushi place we ever been too. Plus, Bat, the owner is the sweetest guy ever. The rolls are hige, the prices are so low for what you get. Amazing! Make sure to go there to see for yourself.

as far as the actual sushi goes, this place is the best in chicago.  Generous poprtions thoughtfully and carefully prepared.  Try the hawaiian roses and of course the Yellowtail special "bat's favorite"
probably the best sushi in chicago! bat - the chef, is SO friendly not to mention he makes amazing sushi. the fish is always so fresh the rolls are huge

After literally having tried Sushi as we know it as well as some authentic japanese style sushi I have to say that Sushi Mon has nailed it! The fish they serve is by far some of the best quality I've been served anywhere, and the creativity doesnt overshadow the flavors at all. They aren't too fussy with the rice or the extra sauces, which the chef/owner Bat makes himself in house, and what they do serve with the fish (if anything at times) compliments the natural taste of the fish very well. I can't speak enough of the caliber of the food they serve up, and they are uber friendly to boot. Bat will actually stop by your table regardless of how busy it is and spend some time getting to know you and your likes/dislikes when it comes to sushi. If you mention not liking a certain type of fish he will make sure that you leave Sushi Mon absoultely in love with it first! Every experience is truly remarkable and unique in its own way as long as you give up all control to the chefs. Kudos!
all you can eat sushi under $20 how can you beat that deal. The service is great. the food is great what else can you ask for!

I have been going to Sushi Mon for the last few years. Their food is excellent and their prices are fair. The service is always great. They are attentive without being overbearing. The special rolls are awesome. I've never been disappointed with them and even had to introduce my cousin from Europe to them because they really are that good.
I absolutely love their Skinny rolls!
Square, pressed sushi you can't find anywhere else.  Worth a try.  Very attentive staff.  Local business; owner/chef is there every night.  Destination sushi in Lincoln Park.
Bat is the best!  He uses the freshest fish and Sushi Mon is an incredible BYOB Sushi Place! The best BYOB sushi in Chicago!

(Translated by Google) I was made aware of this pleasant restaurant of my traveling companions. Since I simply could not cope with American food from the outset and it was increasingly worn down, I gave this shop a chance and was overwhelmed. It was delicious, very nice atmosphere, good service and CHEAP! I'd recommend it to anyone who loves sushi and looking at the corner in vain for some variety.  (Original) Von meinen Reisebegleitern wurde ich auf dieses nette Restaurant aufmerksam gemacht. Da ich von vornherein einfach nicht mit dem amerikanischen Essen zurecht kam und es mich zunehmend zermürbte, gab ich diesem Laden eine Chance und war überwältigt. Es war super lecker, sehr nette Atmosphere, guter Service und GÜNSTIG! Ich kann es Jedem empfehlen, der Sushi liebt und auf der Ecke vergebens nach etwas Abwechslung sucht.

Out of towner craving some sushi. Looked on Google reviews and Sushi Mon was the winner.  Ordered food to go and the server graciously fed me hot soup while waiting. The chef making the sushi was as personable I have encountered in a while. I will be going back and highly recommend this excellent establishment.

My friend and I got a 10pc Alaskan Roll and a deal where we received a 5pc California roll, a Spicy Tuna roll, and a Shrimp Tempura roll for around $28. All of them were tasty and the price was good for the amount of sushi that we got - I'd definitely recommend the place to a friend.
Very delicious and definitely affordable.
Best value sushi! The decor does not offer much, but the rolls do! I think this is one of the only places that does pressed sushi, plus they give you a salad with every role!

Everyone seems to have their own corner sushi place that they love which is not necessarily better than any other place, so I was understandably skeptical when I went here with some friends on their suggestion.  I have to say I was very pleasantly surprised.  I'm not going to be cliche in this review by calling it the best sushi in the city, but it certainly is up there.  It rivals some of the best and more upscale sushi places throughout the city (read: Japonais, Sai, etc.) and at a fraction of the cost.  The owner/chef was happy to make a selection for us on our request, and everything he made was fresh, innovative and delicious.  It's not really a dine in sort of place, but if you manage to get a table you'll enjoy it thoroughly.  Stop by one of the many liquor stores and pick up a bottle of sake or white wine as it's BYOB.  Give it a shot, I'm sure you'll really enjoy it.
